//
// test/sema/resolution/seq_or_parallel_scope.test — SeqOrParallel
// scope fixture (T023 rollover; specs/006-m3-sema/tasks.md Phase 4a).
// Asserts that `seq { … }` blocks open a scope (per data-model §2.1,
// `ScopeKind::SeqOrParallel`) and that names declared in the
// enclosing proc resolve correctly from inside the seq block.
//
// Per `emit-ast-format.contract.md` Invariants 2 + 3 (ASCII
// separators per Invariant 7).

// RUN: printf 'module m {\n  reg q;\n  proc_name p;\n  proc p {\n    seq {\n      q := 0;\n    }\n  }\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK: (ProcDefn {{.*}}name=p
// CHECK: (SeqBlock
// CHECK: (TransferStmt
// CHECK: (IdentifierExpr {{.*}} : BitVector({{[0-9]+}}) {{.*}}-> decl@{{[^:]+}}:2
